// Input runtime, headless coverage.
//
// With no window open, no input events ever arrive (the keyboard/mouse event
// sources are only registered once Screen() opens a display), so every
// keyboard/mouse query returns its zero baseline. This proves each function
// calls through the catalog/libffi path. Interactive behaviour (real key and
// mouse state) is smoke-tested manually via examples/input_demo.cb.

// Keyboard queries by CB scancode (1=Esc, 30=A, 200=Up arrow); EscapeKey().
Print Str(KeyDown(1))
Print Str(KeyUp(30))
Print Str(KeyHit(200))
Print Str(EscapeKey())

// Unmapped / out-of-range scancodes also return 0 (no crash).
Print Str(KeyDown(0))
Print Str(KeyDown(999))

// Mouse buttons (1=left, 2=right, 3=middle): Down/Hit/Up edge queries.
Print Str(MouseDown(1))
Print Str(MouseHit(2))
Print Str(MouseUp(3))

// Wheel position and per-frame movement deltas.
Print Str(MouseZ())
Print Str(MouseMoveX())
Print Str(MouseMoveY())
Print Str(MouseMoveZ())

// Keyboard and mouse queries. Headless: the char/button queues are empty and the arrow
// keys are up, so GetKey/GetMouse and Left/Right/Up/DownKey return 0. WaitKey/
// WaitMouse have no event queue to block on, so they return 0 immediately
// (never hang). ClearKeys/ClearMouse/PositionMouse/ShowMouse are no-ops here.
Print Str(GetKey())
Print Str(LeftKey())
Print Str(RightKey())
Print Str(UpKey())
Print Str(DownKey())
Print Str(WaitKey())
Print Str(GetMouse())
Print Str(WaitMouse())
ClearKeys()
ClearMouse()
PositionMouse(10, 20)
ShowMouse(1)
ShowMouse(0)

Print "done"
